===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|み|yomi=k}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|箕|tr=mi<sub>2</sub>|sort=み}}, perhaps from earlier {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*mui|sort=み}}, which was loaned into {{cog|ain|ムイ|tr=mui|sort=み}} and possibly {{cog|jpx-ryu-pro|*m(u)i|sort=み}}, whence {{cog|xug|箕笊筒|tr=muijōkī|sort=み}} and {{cog|mvi|箕|tr=mui|sort=み}}. In the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', this was used to phonetically write {{m+|ojp|-|w=1}} {{IPAfont|⟨mi<sub>2</sub>⟩}}.

This word had once referred to a squared winnowing basket which originated in northern China and was imported to Japan from Korea.<ref name="Nipponica">{{R:Nipponica|箕}}</ref> However, the exact source of this word is {{unk|ja|nocap=1}}.

